title: Ferrabelo scores pair in South Windsor win
text:
Ferrabelo scores pair in South Windsor win By Journal Inquirer Staff Journal Inquirer | 0 comments 
It may have been a morning game, but the offense of the South Windsor High girls soccer team was wide awake. 
Jaylene Ferrabelo scored two goals as South Windsor coasted to a 5-0 Central Connecticut Conference North win over Bloomfield on Monday. 
Skyler Douglas and Samantha Faust added a goal and an assist apiece for the Bobcats (6-4-0). Zola Mitchell also scored. Hanna Basile made one save for the shutout. Bloomfield is 1-9. kAm$@FE9 (:?5D@C EC2G6=D E@ (6E96CD7:6=5 @? (65?6D52J]k^Am
